Install Gcloud utils
- make sure you have python3
- wget https://dl.google.com/dl/cloudsdk/channels/rapid/downloads/google-cloud-sdk-344.0.0-linux-x86_64.tar.gz
- tar -xvzf google-cloud-sdk-344.0.0-linux-x86_64.tar.gz

- cd google-cloud-sdk; ./install.sh
 press no for feedback.

 It will ask for the profile $path,by default its ~<user>/.bashrc

# To enabled the gcloud command
source ~/.bashrc 

#gcloud init --skip-diagnostics

This will present a URL , chrome this URL this will return a code copy it and paste in the terminal

#Select the projects by number index number

#Select the Regions by number index 


